Mastering Clutch Moments in Call of Duty: 
Search and Destroy
Introduction
Call of Duty: Search and Destroy is a game mode that requires skill, strategy, and composure. 
Clutch moments can often make or break a match, and it is essential to have the right approach 
and tactics to come out on top. In this article, we will discuss five tips to help you improve your 
performance in clutch situations and increase your chances of success.
Tip 1: Stay Calm and Focus on Repositioning
One of the most important aspects of handling clutch moments is maintaining composure. 
Instead of panicking or rushing into a fight, take a moment to reassess the situation. Consider 
repositioning yourself to catch your opponents off guard. By moving to a different side of the 
map, you can create an advantageous position for yourself and increase your chances of winning 
the round.
Tip 2: Utilize Information Gathering
Gaining information about the enemy's location and movements is crucial for making effective 
plays in clutch situations. There are several ways to acquire information, including:
- Using decoy movements to bait enemies into revealing their positions.
- Paying attention to your teammates' locations and the kill feed.
- Listening for audio cues from enemies.
- Utilizing stuns, grenades, or tactical equipment to check rooms or gather information.
By gathering and utilizing information effectively, you can make informed decisions and

increase your chances of successfully clutching a round.
Tip 3: Pay Attention to Time Management
Time management is a critical aspect of clutching moments in Search and Destroy. 
Understanding the timings of planting and defusing the bomb is essential for maximizing your 
chances of success. Remember the following time frames:
- It takes five seconds to plant the bomb.
- It takes seven and a half seconds to defuse the bomb.
If you have planted the bomb and no one is defusing it, it is important not to run around 
aimlessly. Find a hidden spot where you can keep an eye on the bomb and be ready to engage 
any opponents attempting to defuse. Avoid checking the bomb too early if there are only a few 
seconds left, as this gives the enemy a chance to eliminate you and defuse the bomb unnoticed.
Tip 4: Let the Opposing Team Make Mistakes
In clutch situations, both teams are likely to experience nerves and make mistakes. While it is 
crucial to stay calm yourself, remember that your opponents may not be as composed. Allow 
them to make errors and capitalize on them. On defense, avoid unnecessary movements and let 
the aggressors come to you, increasing your chances of winning gunfights. On offense, maintain 
unpredictability, saving Dead Silence for clutch moments, and catch the enemy off guard.
Tip 5: Refine Your Timing in Clutch Moments
Timing is everything in clutch situations. Knowing when to engage, when to reposition, and 
when to strike is vital for success. By practicing and refining your timing, you can make quick 
decisions that catch opponents off guard. This includes using strategies such as pre-aiming, 
utilizing map knowledge, and capitalizing on advantageous positions.
Conclusion
Mastering clutch moments in Call of Duty: Search and Destroy requires a combination of 
composure, strategic thinking, and effective decision-making. By staying calm, acquiring 
information, managing time, and using refined timing, you can greatly increase your chances of 
success in clutch situations. Remember to practice these tips in your gameplay and adapt them to 
your style to become a formidable force in Search and Destroy matches.
A Comprehensive Guide to Modern Warfare 
3 Zombies

Introduction
Modern Warfare Zombies can seem daunting for beginners, but fear not! This beginner's guide 
will provide you with everything you need to know to navigate this mode successfully. From 
selecting your gear to completing missions, we've got you covered.
Selecting Gear
Before you even begin a match, head over to the gear icon on the main menu. Here, you can 
customize your character and choose your gear. You have five slots for gear, including a 
backpack, kill streak, armor plate, gas mask, and self-revive kit. Selecting a primary or 
secondary weapon will take you to another screen where you can choose insurance for the 
weapon, allowing you to bring it into future games. You can also find weapons in the Contraband 
stash, but be careful because if you die with these weapons, you'll lose them permanently.
Dying in Modern Warfare Zombies
If you die in Modern Warfare Zombies, whether it's by zombies or AI soldiers, you'll lose 
everything you had on you, including your insured weapon slots, Contraband weapons, and gear 
in your backpack. You'll have to start from scratch in a future game and find all your loot again.
Tactical, Lethal, and Field Upgrades
In the gear menu, you can also choose your tactical, lethal, and field upgrade. As you progress 
through the game, you'll unlock more field upgrades. Successfully extracting with money, 
valuable items, and Wonder Weapons will convert them into XP, which reduces the cool down 
of your insured weapons.
Acquiring Items and Schematic Crafting
In Modern Warfare Zombies, you can now add items to your backpack through the acquisition 
stash and schematic crafting. The acquisition stash contains rewards like ammo mods, perk cans, 
ether tools, and ether crystals that you can equip in future games. Schematic crafting allows you 
to craft specific items, such as ethereum perks, ammo mods, and Wonder Weapons, by finding 
schematics in-game. Each schematic has a cooldown timer once crafted.
Story Missions
One of the main focuses of Modern Warfare Zombies is the story missions. By selecting a 
mission, completing it, and progressing through the game, you'll unlock rewards, acquisition, and 
XP. Completing all the missions will lead you to a final Story Mission, which features an in-

game cinematic cut scene that progresses the storyline.
Searching for a Match
Once you've customized your gear and selected a mission, you can search for a match. There is a 
squad fill option in the bottom left corner, which can be turned on or off. If you want to play 
solo, turn this option off. However, keep in mind that the game is designed as a 24-player mode, 
so you will always be paired with other players. You can confirm your mission, loadout, and 
ready up to find a match.
Progression in the Game
In the zombies match, you have 45 minutes to explore, complete missions, and take down 
zombies before The Ether storm begins. The map is divided into three difficulty zones: low, 
medium, and high threat. As a beginner, opening your Tac map and looking for contract missions 
near you is recommended. Completing these missions will reward you with points and Rifts, 
which provide various upgrades.
Pack-A-Punch
To progress in the game, you'll need to Pack-A-Punch your weapons and upgrade their rarity. In 
the low threat zone, you can afford to Pack-A-Punch your gun once for 5,000 points. In the 
medium threat zone, complete contracts to earn more points and upgrade your weapon to the 
second Pack-A-Punch level. The third and final Pack-A-Punch upgrade can be obtained in the 
high threat zone for 15,000 points.
Miscellaneous Activities
Throughout the game, you may encounter various distractions and optional activities. You can 
choose to take part in these activities if you wish, but keep in mind your main objective is to 
complete missions and progress through the game.
By following this comprehensive guide, you'll be well-equipped to navigate Modern Warfare 
Zombies. Good luck, and may you survive the hordes of undead!
Guide to Extraction and Advanced 
Techniques in Modern Warfare Zombies
Introduction
In the action-packed game of Modern Warfare Zombies, players are tasked with taking down 
hordes of zombies and extracting safely to retain their progress. This comprehensive guide will

walk you through the extraction process and explore advanced techniques to enhance your 
gameplay.
Extraction Basics
To successfully extract, players must locate one of the three exfil points on the map. These points 
are marked on the map and will always be in low threat zones, making it easier to eliminate the 
zombies in the area. To call in the extraction helicopter, simply approach the exfil point and hold 
the designated button. After a 30-second wait, the helicopter will land, allowing you and your 
teammates to board and complete the extraction.
Rewards and Progression
Upon successfully extracting, players will receive rewards based on their performance in the 
game. If you have found valuable items or schematics, a screen will pop up notifying you of the 
high-value items secured. Additionally, the screen will display the missions completed in the 
game. Any remaining money, Wonder Weapons, or equipment in your inventory will be 
converted into XP, which can be used to cool down your insured weapon slot. Weapons acquired 
during the game will be added to your Contraband stash for future use, while equipped 
backpacks, armor plate carriers, and gas masks can be carried over to the following game.
Advanced Techniques: Mercenary Strongholds and AI 
Activities
Once you are well-equipped, you can explore advanced techniques to enhance your gameplay. 
One such technique is engaging with mercenary encampments. These areas on the map are filled 
with AI soldiers that must be defeated to complete the Merc Camp activity. Defeating these 
soldiers may yield a mercenary stronghold key card, which can be used to access strongholds on 
the map. Strongholds contain safes that must be drilled open while fending off AI and zombies. 
Completing this activity will secure the stronghold and reward you with a fortress key card.
Challenging AI Activities and Boss Battles
One of the most difficult AI activities in Modern Warfare Zombies is the Talanov Outpost.

Marked on the map, this area is guarded by powerful AI soldiers and features a warlord boss 
named Legacy. Defeating Legacy will spawn a Rift containing random loot, which may include 
the new Scorch wonder weapon. For an even greater challenge, players can venture into the high 
threat zone and take on the Mega Abomination, the main mini-boss of the map. This boss 
requires a well-equipped team and strategic gameplay to defeat. It is important to note that the 
Mega Abomination can be guided into the medium threat zone for easier takedowns.
The High Threat Zone and Loot Opportunities
The high threat zone in Modern Warfare Zombies is the most difficult area of the map. The 
zombies in this area have significantly increased health, requiring players to enter with well-
upgraded weapons and perks. It is recommended to approach this area with a vehicle for a quick 
getaway if needed. However, the high threat zone also offers the best loot opportunities, 
including traditional perk machines, the Pack-a-Punch machine, and the mystery box. The later 
you spin the mystery box, the higher the chance of receiving rare and coveted weapons.
Final Extraction and Storm Mechanics
Similar to the DMZ map, Modern Warfare Zombies introduces a final extraction mechanic. 
Players have 45 minutes until the storm consumes the entire map. Using logical reasoning and 
the tag map, players can determine the area that will be consumed by the storm and identify the 
closest exfil points. With approximately 5 minutes remaining, the final exfil point will be 
revealed in an open space near the last swallowed area. As the timer approaches 2 minutes, a 
helicopter will arrive, but it will not depart until the final 10 seconds. Failure to reach the final 
exfil point in time will result in death and the loss of progress.
